  "body": "The npd in hollow-nodes doesn't write its logs to a file despite having its command as:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"/node-problem-detector\",\r\n.....other params....,\r\n\"1>>/var/log/npd-$(NODE_NAME).log 2>&1\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nin hollow-node_template.json. I tried changing it to the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"/bin/sh\",\r\n\"-c\",\r\n\"/node-problem-detector ...params...  (both with and without --logtostderr) 1>>/var/log/npd-$(NODE_NAME).log 2>&1\"     (here the logfile is created but nothing is written to it)\r\n```\r\n\r\nand that makes the container enter crashloop, without providing any way to access logs (I tried looking into /var/log/npd-$(NODE_NAME).log, tried kubectl logs, tried docker logs on the node and also kubectl describe pod, but none of them could give me any useful logs).\r\n\r\n@Random-Liu Any idea how to make npd write to log file in hollow node / why it is failing?\r\n\r\ncc @kubernetes/sig-scalability-misc @wojtek-t @gmarek ",
